  "manufacturing": {
    "method": "chemical synthesis",
    "description": "Produced by neutralizing citric acid with sodium hydroxide or sodium carbonate. The degree of neutralization determines which form is produced: monosodium citrate (E331i), disodium citrate (E331ii), or trisodium citrate (E331iii). Trisodium citrate is the most commonly used form in food applications."
  },
